text.section:
Any corporation formed under this chapter may be dissolved by filing articles of dissolution, which shall be entitled and indorsed "Articles of Dissolution of ...." and shall state:
The name of the corporation and, if it is a consolidated corporation, the names of the original corporations;
The date of filing of the articles of incorporation and, if the corporation is a consolidated corporation, the dates on which the articles of incorporation of the original corporations were filed;
That the corporation elects to dissolve; and
The name and post office address of each of its directors, and the name, title and post office address of each of its officers.
